original: Fransson, Karl Luther, rektor, Alvastra, f. 14/11/95 i Linderås, Jönköp. 1., av lantbr. Frans Gustafsson o. Hilda Johansson. G. 34 m. Sigrun Grey. Barn: Robert f. 35, Lena 36, Anna 37, Brita 40, Inga 42. — Stud:ex. i Lund 17, agronomex. v. Alnarp 20. Ord. ämneslär. v. Törsta lantm:sk. i Jämtl. 1. 20-27, dito v. Hamra lantm:sk. i östergötl. 1. 27-34, tf. förest, där 34, förest. f. östergötl. lantm:sk. v. Höje, Alvastra, sed. 35. Sekr. i o. verkst. ’led. av styr. f. östergötl. biildn:förb. sed. 39, rev. i kommunen, kronoomb. i taxndr.
translated: Fransson, Karl Luther, principal, Alvastra, born on November 14, 1895 in Linderås, Jönköping County, the son of farmer Frans Gustafsson and Hilda Johansson. He married Sigrun Grey in 1934 and they had five children: Robert born in 1935, Lena in 1936, Anna in 1937, Brita in 1940, and Inga in 1942. Fransson completed his studentexamen (secondary school leaving certificate) in Lund in 1917 and his agronomexamen (diploma in agriculture) at Alnarp in 1920. He became an ordinary subject teacher at Törsta agricultural school in Jämtland County from 1920 to 1927, then held the same position at Hamra agricultural school in Östergötland County from 1927 to 1934, where he was also acting manager in 1934, and finally the manager of Höje agricultural school in Alvastra from 1935 onward. Additionally, he acted as a secretary and executive member of the board of the Östergötland Association for Visual Arts starting in 1939, and as a revisionist in the municipality and a tax assessor.
